Definition.WordDefinition: Eliot n 1: British poet (born in the United States) who won the Nobel prize for literature; his plays are outstanding examples of modern verse drama (1888-1965) [syn: {T. S. Eliot}, {Thomas Stearns Eliot}] 2: British writer of novels characterized by realistic analysis of provincial Victorian society (1819-1880) [syn: {George Eliot}, {Mary Ann Evans}]
